snippet.title: Tower of Gold: Barron Trump Sings ON BROADWAY About Donald And Melania's Love (Imagined)
snippet.description:
Tower of Gold 
(A Broadway-style song sung by Barron Trump, playing the role of a charming narrator.)

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics:
In a tower high, with her heels so tall,
A princess waits, looking bored through it all!
She’s got diamonds, pearls, and gowns galore,
But a girl wants more, oh, she wants more! 

She’s trapped in a castle of luxury and grace,
With nothing to do but perfecting her face!
Her kingdom’s a palace, her throne’s a chaise,
But where is the man with the art of the deal? 

Then one day, through the mist of her sorrow,
A prince with a plan and a million to borrow!
With swagger and style and a name in gold,
He knew what he wanted—this story was sold! 

Princess, I’m here, I’m the best in the land!
I’ll build you a tower—you’ll love it, it’s grand!
No need for a ladder, no need for a rope,
I’ll call up my guy, and we’ll build you some hope! 

So he swept her up in a limo so fine,
A wedding so lavish, a love so divine!
From tower to penthouse, her worries all ceased,
For now, she’s a queen—and her kingdom’s increased! 
 And so ends our tale of this love so profound,
When a tower girl met the king of the town! 

(Final note hits. Fireworks. Confetti. A faint “You’re Hired” echoes in the background.)
